## 2. Architecture & File Structure

### 2.1 Source directories (input)
```
project-root/
├── site-config.json          # global settings
├── content.json              # static page content (homepage, about, contact, etc.)
├── data/
│   ├── divisions/            # each file: { id, name, seo?, content? }
│   ├── districts/            # each file: { id, name, division_id, seo?, content? }
│   ├── tehsils/              # each file: { id, name, district_id, seo?, content? }
│   ├── depots/               # each file: { id, name, tehsil_id, villages, contact?, address?, seo?, content? }
│   ├── related-depots/       # each file: { depots_id, related_depots: [...] } or array format
│   ├── blogs/                # each file: .json with { title, date, content (markdown), excerpt?, author?, tags?, seo? }
│   ├── ads.json              # optional – array of ad objects { name, script, show }
├── assets/
│   ├── img/                  # all images (favicon.*, logo, blog images)
│   ├── urls/                 # .js files containing URL constants (e.g., const BOOKING_URL = "...")
├── templates/                # (optional, currently unused but created)
```

### 2.2 Output directories (generated)
```
public/
├── index.html
├── about.html, contact.html, terms.html, privacy.html, disclaimer.html
├── blogs/
│   ├── index.html            # blog listing
│   ├── <blog-id>.html        # individual blog posts
├── <division-id>/index.html
├── <division-id>/<district-id>/index.html
├── <division-id>/<district-id>/<tehsil-id>/index.html
├── <division-id>/<district-id>/<tehsil-id>/<depot-id>/index.html
├── assets/
│   ├── images/               # copied from assets/img (except favicons)
│   ├── urls/url-constants.js # compiled URL constants for client side
├── search-index.js           # JSON search index wrapped in window.searchIndex
├── sitemap.xml
├── robots.txt
└── favicon files (favicon.ico, favicon.png, etc.) placed at root
```

### 2.3 Generation flow (class `SiteGenerator`)
1. **Constructor** – creates necessary directories, copies images & URL constants to public, loads config, content, ads, blogs, URL constants, all data files, and related depots.
2. **generateSite()** – calls methods to generate all page types, sitemap, robots.txt, search index, URL constants file.
3. **Output** – static HTML/CSS/JS ready to serve.

