## 3. Data Models (JSON Schemas)

### 3.1 `site-config.json`
```json
{
  "base_url": "https://example.com",
  "site_name": "MSRTC Bus Timetable",
  "theme": {
    "bg_gradient_start": "#F5F3FF",
    "bg_gradient_end": "#EDE9FE"
  },
  "ads": {
    "top_ad": { "enabled": false, "code": "...", "mobile_code": "...", "desktop_code": "..." },
    "middle_ad": { ... },
    "footer_ad": { ... }
  }
}
```

### 3.2 `content.json`
```json
{
  "homepage": {
    "title": "...",
    "subtitle": "...",
    "content": "<p>...</p>",
    "seo": { "title": "...", "description": "...", "keywords": "..." }
  },
  "about": { "title": "...", "content": "...", "seo": {...} },
  "contact": { ... },
  "terms": { ... },
  "privacy": { ... },
  "disclaimer": { ... }
}
```

### 3.3 Division, District, Tehsil files
Each file in `data/divisions/`, `data/districts/`, `data/tehsils/` is named `<id>.json`:
```json
{
  "id": "pune",
  "name": "Pune Division",
  "alphabet": "P",           // optional, defaults to first char of name
  "seo": { "title": "...", "description": "...", "keywords": "..." },
  "content": {               // optional
    "description": "...",
    "seo_content": { "title": "...", "content": "...", "faqs": [...] }
  }
}
```
**Relationships**:
- District → `division_id` (string referencing division id)
- Tehsil → `district_id`

### 3.4 Depot file (`data/depots/<id>.json`)
```json
{
  "id": "pune_city",
  "name": "Pune City Depot",
  "tehsil_id": "pune_city_tehsil",
  "address": "Near Swargate, Pune",
  "contact": "020-1234567",
  "villages": {
    "S": [                                   // key = first letter of bus stop name
      {
        "name": "Shivajinagar Bus Stop",
        "schedule": ["05:30", "06:45", "08:00", "17:20", "18:45"]
      }
    ],
    "K": [...]
  },
  "seo": { ... },
  "content": {
    "about": "<p>Description of depot...</p>",
    "faqs": [
      { "question": "What is the first bus?", "answer": "..." }
    ],
    "seo_content": { ... }
  }
}
```
- `villages`: object grouped by first letter (uppercase) of bus stop name.
- Each bus stop has `name` (string) and `schedule` (array of "HH:MM" strings in 24‑hour format).

### 3.5 Related depots (`data/related-depots/*.json`)
Two supported formats:
```json
// Format 1 (array, new with hierarchy)
[
  {
    "depots_id": "pune_city",
    "related_depots": [
      { "depot_id": "swargate", "division_id": "pune", "district_id": "pune", "tehsil_id": "pune_city" }
    ]
  }
]

// Format 2 (single object, old)
{
  "depots_id": "pune_city",
  "related_depots_id": ["swargate", "katraj"]
}
```
The generator resolves missing hierarchy from actual depot data.

### 3.6 Blog file (`data/blogs/<id>.json`)
```json
{
  "title": "New Timetable from April 2025",
  "date": "2025-04-01",
  "updated": "2025-04-02",
  "author": "MSRTC Admin",
  "excerpt": "Summary of changes...",
  "tags": ["timetable", "update"],
  "content": "Markdown text with # headers, **bold**, `code`, ![alt](image.jpg), [text](URL_CONSTANT)",
  "seo": { "title": "...", "description": "...", "keywords": "..." },
  "seo_content": { ... }
}
```
**Markdown processing** (in `processBlogContent()`):
- Code blocks (```) → preserved with `escapeHtml`
- Inline code → `<code>`
- Headers (`#` to `######`) → `<h1>` … `<h6>`
- Bold `**text**` / `__text__` → `<strong>`
- Italic `*text*` / `_text_` → `<em>`
- Tables (pipe‑separated) → `<table>` with alignment from header row
- Lists (`-`, `*`, `+` or numbered) → `<ul>`/`<ol>`
- Links `[text](url)` – if `url` matches `[A-Z0-9]+` (URL constant) → `<a href="javascript:void(0);" data-constant="...">`
- Images `![alt](path)` → `<div class="blog-image-container">` with responsive image. If path is relative, image is copied from `assets/img/` to `public/assets/images/`.
- Blockquotes (`> text`) → `<blockquote>`
- Horizontal rules (`---`, `***`, `___`) → `<hr>`

### 3.7 Ads (`data/ads.json`)
```json
[
  { "name": "Google Adsense", "script": "<script async src='...'></script>", "show": true }
]
```
These scripts are injected into `<head>` of every page via `renderHeadScripts()`.

### 3.8 URL constants (`assets/urls/*.js`)
Example `booking.js`:
```javascript
const BOOKING_URL = "https://msrtc.maharashtra.gov.in/booking";
const HELPLINE = "1800-123-4567";
```
Generator extracts `const NAME = "value"` pairs and writes `window.URL_CONSTANTS` object into `public/assets/urls/url-constants.js`.

