## 4. UI & Front‑end Features

### 4.1 Layout components (all pages)
- **Fixed header** with site logo and real‑time digital clock (IST, updated every second).
- **Vertical alphabet navigation** (fixed right side, scrollable) – letters A–Z.
  - Clicking a letter scrolls to the first card / bus stop section starting with that letter.
  - Disabled letters (no content) are greyed out.
  - Active letter is highlighted during scroll.
- **Search bar** – filters divisions/districts/tehsils/depots (homepage tabs) or bus stops (depot page).
- **Ad containers** (top, middle, footer) with mobile/desktop responsive switching.
- **Footer** with links to static pages, official MSRTC sites, and copyright.

### 4.2 Homepage tabs
- Four tabs: Divisions, Districts, Tehsils, Depots.
- Each tab shows a grid of **rectangular cards** with name, parent location (if any), and statistics (e.g., number of depots).
- Cards link to the respective detail page.
- Tabs preserve active state in `localStorage` and URL hash.

### 4.3 Depot detail page (core feature)
- Depot header: name, address, contact, total bus stops, total buses.
- **Search bar** – filters bus stops by name.
- **Time filters** (All, 5AM‑12PM, 12PM‑5PM, 5PM‑10PM, 10PM‑5AM) – shows/hides time bubbles.
- **Bus stop sections** – each bus stop has a name and a grid of **time bubbles** (colour‑coded by time of day).
  - Clicking a bubble alerts the time and bus stop name.
  - **Next bus** logic:
    - Every 30 seconds, recalculates upcoming buses within the next **60 minutes** (configurable in JS).
    - The nearest bus gets a `NEXT` badge; others get a `+Xm` badge.
    - A sparkle animation highlights the bubble.
- **About section** (from depot `content.about`) – HTML allowed.
- **FAQ section** (from depot `content.faqs`).
- **Related depots** – cards linking to other depots (from `related-depots/` or fallback to same tehsil).

### 4.4 Blog pages
- Listing page (`blogs/index.html`) shows cards with title, excerpt, date.
- Individual blog page includes author avatar, date, content (processed HTML), tags, and SEO content.
- Blog links that use URL constants (e.g., `[Book Ticket](BOOKING_URL)`) are handled by JavaScript – they open the constant URL in a new tab.

### 4.5 Responsive CSS (mobile‑first)
- Breakpoints:
  - `< 768px` (mobile) – single column cards, smaller font, compact time bubbles.
  - `768px – 1024px` (tablet) – two‑column grid.
  - `> 1024px` (desktop) – three‑column grid.
- Right padding on `.container` accounts for vertical alphabet strip (28px mobile, 30px tablet, 32px desktop) so content never hides behind it.
- Cards, search bar, and bus stop sections are full‑width and properly aligned.
- Print styles remove navigation, ads, and alphabet nav.

