## 6. Generation Process Details

### 6.1 Image & favicon handling
- All images from `assets/img/` are copied to `public/assets/images/`.
- Favicon files (detected by name containing “favicon” or “icon”, or extension `.ico`) are copied to `public/` root.
- Any old favicon files in `public/` are deleted before copying (to avoid duplicates).

### 6.2 Page rendering hierarchy
- **Division page** – lists all districts in that division (cards).
- **District page** – lists all tehsils in that district, shows parent division.
- **Tehsil page** – lists all depots in that tehsil, shows parent district & division.
- **Depot page** – detailed view (as described).
- Each page includes breadcrumb‑style navigation buttons (“Back to …”).

### 6.3 Search index generation
`generateSearchIndex()` creates `public/search-index.js`:
```javascript
window.searchIndex = {
  divisions: [ { id, name, type, path, districts, depots, alphabet } ],
  districts: [ { id, name, type, path, division, tehsils, depots, alphabet } ],
  tehsils: [ { ... } ],
  depots: [ { id, name, type, path, division, district, tehsil, busStops, buses, alphabet } ]
}
```
Used by the global search modal.

### 6.4 Sitemap & robots.txt
- `sitemap.xml` includes all generated pages (home, static, blogs, divisions, districts, tehsils, depots) with priorities and change frequencies.
- `robots.txt` allows all user agents, disallows `/data/`, and points to the sitemap.

### 6.5 Ads injection
`renderHeadScripts()` loops over `this.ads` (loaded from `data/ads.json`) and outputs the `script` for any ad where `show === true`.
Additionally, `renderAd()` places top/middle/footer ad containers (from `site-config.json` ads) with responsive code.

