## 7. Execution & Usage

### 7.1 Requirements
- Node.js (any modern version)
- No external npm dependencies – uses only `fs` and `path` core modules.

### 7.2 Running the generator
```bash
node site-generator.js
```
This will:
1. Read all source files.
2. Generate the entire static site into `public/` folder.
3. Output console logs for each step.

### 7.3 Deployment
The `public/` folder can be served by any static web server (Apache, Nginx, Vercel, Netlify, GitHub Pages, etc.).

